article.headline: Detroit 65, Youngstown State 54
article.story: YOUNGSTOWN, Ohio (AP) -- Brandon Cotton scored 22 points and Detroit shot 52 percent from the field in beating Youngstown State 65-54 on Wednesday night. Chuck Bailey added 16 points and Torvoris Baker added seven points and 12 rebounds for the Titans (13-14, 7-7 Horizon League). Quin Humphrey had 17 points and Derrick Harris 14 for the Penguins (7-17, 4-10), who made just 32 percent of their field goal attempts. Ahead 35-32 at the half, the Titans took control by running off the first seven points of the second half. Baker had a tip-in and a dunk, Cotton hit a free throw and Bailey made a jumper during the spurt. Youngstown State cut the lead to four points on a Humphrey 3-pointer with 5 minutes left before Cotton hit a jumper and a 3-pointer to help the Titans pull away again.
